article.headline: Army 61, Dartmouth 54
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. -- Cleveland Richard scored 20 points and hit a 3-pointer with just over a minute left, helping Army on a big late run to beat Dartmouth 61-54 on Saturday night. The Black Knights (4-9) outscored Dartmouth (2-10) 21-4 over the final 7:22, overcoming a 10-point deficit to snap a two-game skid and win their second road game of the season. Freshman guard Julian Simmons made his first career start for Army and had 15 points on 6-of-11 shooting. Alex Barnett led the Big Green with 17 points and seven rebounds. Clive Weeden added 10 points, all in the second half.
